<br>
We want to know your thoughts, needs, likes, etc.<br>
<br>
So far we have had the following suggestions.  Please feel free to comment.<br>
<br>
1. A character database that will let us know who peoples and their alts are.  In the case of Camelot I can probably update levels automatically from the Herald.  Photos of the character can be added.<br>
<br>
2. Player of the week.  We follow one player around both in and out of the game (depending on participation of the person themselves and how much personal information they are willing to divulge).<br>
<br>
3. The Roving Reporter interview.  The Roving Reporter does an interview with a player or a character every week.<br>
<br>
4. A story board.  We gather up all the stories from the board and place them in one database on the site.<br>
<br>
5. Integrate the board.  I know that Krys wasn't keen on moving the board over to the FT site, but we might be able to embed the EZ-Board into a pane.  I am looking into the possibility of this.<br>
<br>
6. FT theme and new logos.  The current theme is PostNuke.  We could customise the graphics to reflect a more Forgotten truth feel.  A new Forgotten Truth logo would be part of this change. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/ufarmelle.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Farmelle</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://www.horsford.force9.co.uk/Icon.gif" BORDER=0> at: 4/18/02 9:58:49 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6B8E23><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> Your Roving Reporter</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br> <font color=#5F9EA0>(4/18/02 9:39:34 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub10.ezboard.com/fforgottentruthforeignlegiongeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1060.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> !!!</span><hr size=1> Did somebody mention my name?<br>
Have you ever seen any of my previous postings?<br>
Who in their right mind would want me to do an article on them? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> Wamba</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br> <font color=#5F9EA0>(4/18/02 9:56:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub10.ezboard.com/fforgottentruthforeignlegiongeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1060.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> reply</span><hr size=1> Back when the Forgotten Truth branched out into AC, and created the Foreign Legion, we got this site to cover subjects that were not EQ related.<br>
Since then, I have prefered this sight for one reason, and one reason only; It is simple and easy to use.<br>
I am lazy!  And technologicaly challenged!  I have never seen the need to invest much time in figuring out how to use a high-tech guild site, when this one is soooo easy.<br>
So for any other guild site, please keep in mind the KISS theory for players like me.<br>
<br>
Keep<br>
It<br>
