Stupid <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6B8E23><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/ufarmelle.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Farmelle</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://www.horsford.force9.co.uk/Icon.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#5F9EA0>(4/18/02 10:21:56 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub10.ezboard.com/fforgottentruthforeignlegiongeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1060.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.horsford.force9.co.uk/Photo.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: reply</span><hr size=1> I have two current complaints about the site.<br>
<br>
Firstly I want to be presented with a &quot;LOGON/REGISTER NOW&quot; button at the top left if I am not logged on. (EDIT:  Which I just fixed.  YAY me!)<br>
<br>
Secondly is content.  We have to put content there to make it worth while.  Content has to be changed on a daily, or at least weekly basis to keep the site useful.<br>
<br>
Other ideas I have for content are :-<br>
<br>
1. Vault Clearance.  A list of items in your vault that you want to get rid of.  You can list what everyone has and if you see anything that takes your fancy you just have to click and it auto sends a mail to that person telling them that you want it.<br>
<br>
2. Crafting Requests.  A list of crafter based stuff that you want.  Somewhere that the guild Artisans can look and say &quot;Oh X wants Y, I can make that for them while I am in the area.&quot;  Saves you having to catch the person on-line.<br>
<br>
I will add more as I think of them.  I agree with Uncle Wamba that this board is nice and easy to use, but I feel that we need a little more than the ability to leave messages.  I am in no way saying that we should dump the board but I believe that there is more information that could be conveyed.  The links section for example the site now mirrors all the links that Krys has posted and I can check if they are still valid on a weekly basis.<br>
<br>
Once I move and get my ADSL in at my new home (12 days) I will be able to put an hour or so a day into new content and features for the site, for free as well and trust me when I say my time isn't cheap <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    I think this is worth pursuing if only to see what we get at the end of it all. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/ufarmelle.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Farmelle</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://www.horsford.force9.co.uk/Icon.gif" BORDER=0> at: 4/18/02 11:02:01 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/ucreepypete.showPublicProfile?language=EN>CreepyPete</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#5F9EA0>(4/18/02 12:27:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub10.ezboard.com/fforgottentruthforeignlegiongeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1060.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: reply</span><hr size=1> I'd love to see Camelot News and Patch Messages continue to be posted on the board. Gaming related sites are locked down at my work, so I usually just pull them outta Google's web cache if I really HAVE to see something before I get home. It's really nice to be able to look them up on our site.<br>
